\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0
\par\plain {\f1\fs24\b0\i1 Check the room:}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Zima: (It\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92s a training field that annexes HQ. The Cadets are polishing their equipment, supervised by the Marshal.)}
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0
\par\plain {\f1\fs24\b0\i1 Talk to the Marshal (Marshal Karl):}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 On first time talking:}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Zima: (Karl is a retired Captain. Now he just trains recruits, but he takes his work in stride.)}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Karl: \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Lady Zima! Head of the King\u8217\'92s Justice. An honour to have you on my grounds. What can I help you with?\u8221\'94}
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0
\par\plain {\f1\fs24\b0\i1 else :}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Karl: \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Lady Zima. What can I help you with?\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 \}}
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 ASK ABOUT THE HEADQUARTERS}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 ASK ABOUT THE BROKERING DEAL}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 ASK ABOUT THE KING}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 ASK ABOUT THE NEW RECRUITS}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 SAY GOODBYE}
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0
\par\plain {\f1\fs24\b0\i1 Ask about the headquarters:}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Zima: \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Is everything in order at the HQ?\u8221\'94}
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Karl: \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Yes, although the others are anxious about the Prince\u8217\'92s meeting with the Confederacy.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0
\par\plain {\f1\fs24\b0\i1 Ask about the brokering deal:}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Zima: \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93What\u8217\'92s your opinion of the King\u8217\'92s brokering deal?\u8221\'94}
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Karl: \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Those are matters beyond myself, Lady Zima. I trust in the King and the Prince.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0
\par\plain {\f1\fs24\b0\i1 Ask about the King:}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Zima: \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93How do you feel about the King\u8217\'92s mental state?\u8221\'94}
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0
\par\plain {\f1\fs24\b0\i1 First time:}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Karl: \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Lady Zima! I\u8217\'92ll pretend I didn\u8217\'92t hear that. The King is fine. I know it\u8217\'92s been a while since you\u8217\'92ve seen him, but don\u8217\'92t listen to the rumors.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0
\par\plain {\f1\fs24\b0\i1 If later:}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Karl: \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Lady Zima, I know it\u8217\'92s been a while since you\u8217\'92ve seen him, but don\u8217\'92t listen to the rumors.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0
\par\plain {\f1\fs24\b0\i1 Ask about the new recruits:}
\par\plain {\f1\fs24\b0\i1 If now:}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Zima: \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93How are the trainees?\u8221\'94}
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Karl: \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Could be better. The latest batch of recruits don\u8217\'92t keep up pace, and their loyalty to the King is\u8230\'85 disappointing.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0
\par\plain {\f1\fs24\b0\i1 If later:}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Zima: \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93How are the trainees coming along?\u8221\'94}
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Karl: \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93They respond well to simulated fighting, but shirk at the real thing. This group isn\u8217\'92t much, I\u8217\'92m afraid.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Karl: \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93I bet they would respond well to a few minutes in the ring with you Lady Zima--if they could last that long, of course.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 TAKE ONE ON}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 TAKE TWO ON}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 TAKE THREE ON}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 DECLINE}
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0
\par\plain {\f1\fs24\b0\i1 After every choice to fight:}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Karl: \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Excellent, Lady Zima! I\u8217\'92m sure this is just what these cadets need. Take these rubber bullets for the exercise. And, don\u8217\'92t go too easy on them.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 BATTLE!}
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0
\par\plain {\f1\fs24\b0\i1 After a successful battle:}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Karl: \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Excellent job Lady Zima. That should help them build some character. Here\u8217\'92s a little something for your help. And feel free to show these recruits the what-for anytime.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0
\par\plain {\f1\fs24\b0\i1 On failing the battle:}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Karl: \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Hey, don\u8217\'92t get full of yourselves out there! Count yourselves lucky that Lady Zima went easy on you! I won\u8217\'92t be so nice.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0
\par\plain {\f1\fs24\b0\i1 Say goodbye:}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Karl: Good luck with the investigation, Lady Zima.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 \}}
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0
\par\plain {\f1\fs24\b0\i1 Go to the Restraining Cells:}
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 CHECK THE ROOM}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 CHECK THE CELL DISPLAYS}
