\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Zima: \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93I\u8217\'92m in the Restraining Cells. What should I do?\u8221\'94}
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0
\par\plain {\f1\fs24\b0\i1 Check the room:}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Zima: \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93These cells hold smugglers, robbers and criminal suspects. I\u8217\'92d say I\u8217\'92m responsible for a quarter of the people here.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0
\par\plain {\f1\fs24\b0\i1 Check the cell displays:}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Zima: \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93There are detention blocks ahead. The detainees inside are without parole until their investigations are finished.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0
\par\plain {\f1\fs24\b0\i1 Check the prisoners:}
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Zima: \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Right now there\u8217\'92s nobody in these cells relevant to my current cases.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 \}}
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0
\par\plain {\f1\fs24\b0\i1 Go to the Interrogation Room:}
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 CHECK THE ROOM}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 CHECK THE NEWS DISPLAY}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 TALK TO MARSHAL MOTHRS}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 RETURN TO THE ENTRANCE HALL}
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Zima: \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93I\u8217\'92m in the Interrogation Room. What should I do?\u8221\'94}
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0
\par\plain {\f1\fs24\b0\i1 Check the room:}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Zima: \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93This is where interrogations and profiling work are done. Investigations with suspects and arrested criminals take place here.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0
\par\plain {\f1\fs24\b0\i1 Check the news display:}
\par\plain {\f1\fs24\b0\i1 First:}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 News Feed: \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93PRINCE TO BROKER PEACE DEAL WITH CONFEDERACY. It's expected that the trade deal ensures a cleaner and more efficient conversion rate in future resources exchanges between the Confederacy and the Kingdom."}
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0
\par\plain {\f1\fs24\b0\i1 Then later:}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 News Feed: "EX-RANK SOLDIERS FORMING GANGS ON THE OUTER RIM? Several reports indicate that the gangs of the Outer Rim of the Kingdom's space are gaining members from the State of The Rank. Should it be true, this would be a black omen in crime related activities in said zones."}
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0
\par\plain {\f1\fs24\b0\i1 Talk to Marshal Mothrs:}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 First time initiating conversation:}
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Zima (Marshal Mothrs is the lead prosecutor of the capital. Despite his title he\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92s a fairly casual talker. And well loyal.)}
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Zima: \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Greetings, Marshal. The King has asked me to leave for the Outer Rim colonies. I trust you'll keep everything in order."}
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0
\par\plain {\f1\fs24\b0\i1 If wearing silly clothes:}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Mothrs: \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Heavens, Zima, you look like a mess. Come back when you\u8217\'92re properly dressed.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0
\par\plain {\f1\fs24\b0\i1 If wearing other outfit:}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Mothrs: \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Just, good to see you. Also, odd choice of clothing. What do you need?\u8221\'94}
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0
\par\plain {\f1\fs24\b0\i1 If wearing professional outfit:}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Mothrs: \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Just, good to see you. What do you need?\u8221\'94}
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 ASK ABOUT THE AUGMENTATION GANGS}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 ASK ABOUT THE MURDER CASE}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 ASK ABOUT THE BROKERING DEAL}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 ASK ABOUT THE KING}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 SAY GOODBYE}
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0
\par\plain {\f1\fs24\b0\i1 Ask about the augmentation gangs:}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Zima: \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93What can you tell me about the aug deals and gangs in the Capital?\u8221\'94}
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Mothrs: \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93All of our investigations are leading to one provider that we can\u8217\'92t coax out of hiding. I\u8217\'92ll get Xeed to send you more details.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0
\par\plain {\f1\fs24\b0\i1 Ask about the murder case:}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Zima: \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93What happened to the murder of the socialite?\u8221\'94}
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Mothrs: \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93The King has made it a priority to figure that out. We need to figure out just what kind of foul play took place. I\u8217\'92ll let you know if we need help.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0
\par\plain {\f1\fs24\b0\i1 Ask about the brokering deal:}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Zima: \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Did the King issue special protection orders for today\u8217\'92s deal?\u8221\'94}
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Mothrs: \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93We suggested it, but the Prince has his own protection, and insisted that he feels safe.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0
\par\plain {\f1\fs24\b0\i1 Ask about the King:}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Zima: \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Did the King say anything else about the deal?\u8221\'94}
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Mothrs: \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93No, but I could tell he doesn\u8217\'92t have a good feeling about it. He\u8217\'92s even less composed than usual.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Zima: \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Keep faith in the King, Mothrs.\u8221\'94 }
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Mothrs: \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Just\u8230\'85 consider what he asks of you.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Zima: \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93That\u8217\'92s not my job.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Zima: (Mothrs stops clicking the pen in his hand for a moment, then softens. He seems eager to change the subject.)}
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0
\par\plain {\f1\fs24\b0\i1 Say goodbye:}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Mothrs: \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Good luck, Just.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0
\par\plain {\f1\fs24\b0\i1 If there has been an accident:}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Corporal: \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Mothrs, Zima, there has been an accident!\u8221\'94}
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Mothrs: \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93The meeting--there has been an accident!\u8221\'94}
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Zima: (We move to the entrance hall where a crowd of employees have gathered around a monitor.)}
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Reporter: \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93As we have reported there has been an accident at the brokering deal between the Kingdom and the Confederacy.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Reporter: \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Officials are reporting that an explosion went off inside the building. Multiple casualties have been confirmed but none have been identified.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Zima: \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93I need to go there, now.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Corporal: \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Hang on Zima. I received a message from the Palace before I arrived. There\u8217\'92s one other thing the public doesn\u8217\'92t know. The Prince is dead.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Mothrs: \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Shit\u8230\'85 what does this mean for the treaty?\u8221\'94}
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Corporal: \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Nothing good.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Zima: (I try to say something but the words don\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92t come. I sit down, slowly. There is a cloud over me, like when I was young. I think of the Prince, the King. The Kingdom. And then I know there is no time left to think like this.)}
